<br>
Through a twist of fate I became a cleric here...  I enjoy it, but I do miss the carefree life of the rogue.   Healing is a stressfull job.  I have several mentors who teach me strategies, but I also experiment on my own.  <br>
<br>
Coming from a rogue's background, a cleric can hunt alone anytime he wants.  I never really could when a rogue.  <br>
<br>
Anyhow, I've reached 35th level, and keep me tinker's healed as best I can.  It's tough sometimes when I'm the only cleric and there are about 10 of us hunting in a dungeon.  I am proud to say though that we had no deaths the last time we ran through runnyeye.   The other day we were using stalking probes to scout within the dungeon of solsek's eye safely.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As for groups... I think sucess can be had with any diverse combination of players.  Healing prevents downtime at a minimum... or allows you to take on something much tougher.  A rogue is like a pet that won't get attacked... free, fast damage.  Bards make the group fight stronger in my experience.  Another good example was a group I was in in sebilis... Shaman, Rogue, Bard, Necromancer, Cleric, Enchanter.  At one point we had no less than 15 frogloks in the room, and the Bard, Necro, and Enchanter managed to keep them all under control.  It was a sight to see.<br>
 <br>
As a rogue, I played in an amazingly diverse set of situations.  Many of them arose from just trying to make something work with who we had available.  Some places can be done without clerics, shamen, enchanters, bards, and other classes... some favor one class over another... to me it depends on your tactics and the skill of the players.  People never would let me pull or scout much, Even though I loved to be the scout... Most folks &quot;knew&quot; how to hunt a zone and would take no chances, do no dungeon crawls, would setup tents and camp.  Boring heh.  <br>
<br>
Anyhow, in the end my transformation to a gnome of the cloth has been rough, but I feel I play the healer adequately.  I've finally stopped trying to circle around the backside of the monsters.  People send me /tells all night long for groups... almost too much.  I suppose we are a rare breed, or stay lower profile. <p><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, Cleric of the Tinker's Pride<br>Linguist, Master of Tinkering and Pottery

